Planning a Visit?

Calling on Genuine Smithfield, Virginia is like watching your sultry date come slowly down her winding staircase. It's a visit to a simpler time when folks greeted one another on the street and life went by at a slower pace, a place that envelopes you in its arms and makes you say, "ahhhhh". The town abounds in genuine history, genuine charm and even genuine characters. So savor your visit to Genuine Smithfield where you'll feel as if you've come home.

Smithfield Country Ham

The famous Smithfield cure and aging process has not changed since the early Colonial days. Distinctive Smithfield Hams were among the New World's first exports, gracing the tables of European royalty and nobility.

Shop Downtown Smithfield

In the November 2007 issue of Southern Living Magazine, Wharf Hill was selected as one of the Top 50 Shops in the South. They had showcased this store in their magazine before, but this designation really made Smithfield proud. Being one of the favorite 50 shops from Florida to Maryland, and from Virginia to Texas, is an honor.

Welcome to the Town of Smithfield's Official Website

Smithfield, Virginia

Located in Isle of Wight County, Smithfield has a population of approximately 8,100 (2010 Census population - 8,089) and is approximately 10.1 square miles in size. Smithfield offers residents a small-town atmosphere, a good school system, affordable housing, a historic downtown, and a new state-of-the-art community/conference center - The Smithfield Center. According to the Virginia Review, Smithfield is "without a doubt, one of the prettiest towns in Virginia." Learn More About Smithfield >
